  <h1> What states are safest?</h1>
  <h3> Useful Definitions </h3>
  <div id="definition">
  <p>
    <h5> Death by unnatural causes: </h5> An untimely death brought about by methods other than natural, bodily causes, such as sickness or old age
    <br>
      <br>
    <h5> Cause of death by unnatural causes: </h5> The tool or action that brought about an unnatural death such as a cut, a firearm, or a fire
    <br>
      <br>
    <h5> Ratio: </h5> The amount of people who die by unnatural causes in a given state per year divided by the amount of people who live in the state
    <br>
      <br>
    <h5> Macrodata: </h5> The data describing a big territory, here, the United States
    <br>
      <br>
    <h5> Microdata: </h5> The data describing a smaller territory, here, a specific state
    <br>

  </p>
</div>
